Sheep pox and goat pox, Israel
------------------------------
Information received on 28 Apr 2011 from Dr Michel Bellaiche,
Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan, Israel

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 14 Apr 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 26 Apr 2011
Report date 28 Apr 2011
Date submitted to OIE 28 Apr 2011
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 10 Mar 2011
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Sheep pox virus
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (Kafar Qasem) Kafar Qasem, Petach-Tiqwa, Hamerkaz
Date of start of the outbreak 14 Apr 2011
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Village
Species Sheep
Susceptible 60
Cases 10
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0

Affected Population: A herd of mixed breed sheep. 10 ewes were
affected with typical lesions on the skin.

Epidemiology - Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection:
Illegal movement of animals

Control measures - Measures applied: Quarantine; Movement control
inside the country; Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s); No
treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied - No other measures

Laboratory name and type: Kimron Veterinary Institute (National
laboratory)

Species Sheep
Test electron microscopy
Test date
Result Pending

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

